Pre-Game Insights: England will play their penultimate fixture of the 2023 World Cup group stage against Netherlands at the MCA Stadium in Pune on 8 November.
With just one win in their first seven games, England's World Cup defense was in tatters as they played Australia in Ahmedabad.
Netherlands suffered a disappointing loss to Afghanistan in their latest match but will be looking to win a third match and cement qualification for the 2025 Champions Trophy.
England and Netherlands have faced off on 6 occasions in ODIs, with England winning all 6 times.
Netherlands have been one of the most tactically astute teams in the tournament, even if they haven't quite put together all facets of their game yet.
England have performed well below expectations but will probably still start as favourites.

There has been enough evidence throughout this World Cup to suggest a Netherlands win could very much be on the cards, and they will definitely run England close but the 2019 world champions should still emerge victorious.
